The paper discusses the integration of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) into Estimation of Distribution Algorithms (EDAs) for solving combinatorial optimization problems. This involves the use of neural networks and machine learning techniques, which are typically covered in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also deals with optimization problems, which fall under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
